Klara builds on the third-party datasets listed below. These datasets are NOT
vendored in this repository — they are acquired separately and loaded into the
database at deploy time by the scripts under backend/src/klara/scripts/. This
file records the attribution obligations that apply once the data is loaded.

================================================================================
German noun gender oracle
================================================================================
Source:   gambolputty/german-nouns
          https://github.com/gambolputty/german-nouns
License:  Creative Commons Attribution-ShareAlike 4.0 International (CC BY-SA 4.0)
          https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/4.0/
Used by:  backend/src/klara/scripts/load_de_gender.py -> the `gender_lexicon` table.
Changes:  lemma and grammatical gender are extracted; genus (m/f/n) is mapped to
          the articles der/die/das; on duplicate lemmas the last row wins.

CC BY-SA 4.0 is a share-alike license: gender data derived from this dataset
(the contents of the `gender_lexicon` table, and any redistribution thereof)
remains licensed under CC BY-SA 4.0. The Klara source code itself is MIT and is
unaffected by this obligation.

